Pawtucket.Winsor\u2013Swan\u2013Whitman Farm:
The Winsor–Swan–Whitman Farm is an historic house at 416 Eaton Street in Providence, Rhode Island. The farmhouse was built in 1750 and added to the National Register of Historic Places in 1974.


== Location ==
When it was constructed in 1748, the property was located on the northwest limit of the Providence city line, in a region commonly referred to as Elmhurst.
